    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** offense is anchored today by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 83.29. Facing McCullers Jr., **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an optimal intersection of a favorable park factor (+16%) and a weak SP_xERA of 4.94. His potential for stolen bases is maximized against a pitcher with a historically slow delivery, and his leadoff spot ensures maximum plate appearance volume. Similarly, **Jacob Wilson** (74.08) projects as an elite play; the favorable matchup against Cameron and the +10% park boost make him a high-floor, high-ceiling option in the shortstop slot. We are also capitalizing on **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.02), whose power profile against Ober is bolstered by a strong xwOBA (0.384) and a beneficial batting order position.\n\nOur most critical decision involves **Nasim Nunez** (47.72) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.56) against Peralta. While **Nasim Nunez** sits in the marginal tier, his inclusion is a strategic imperative in our quest to mitigate the scarcity of stolen bases. His score is artificially capped by his lower batting order position, but the +4% boost attributed to the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery to the plate makes him a necessary asset. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** serves as our primary offensive engine in the middle infield, leveraging a 14% platoon advantage to comfortably clear the 60-point threshold. Conversely, **Drake Baldwin** (54.14) and **Heliot Ramos** (54.96) remain start-worthy despite challenging matchups against Valdez and Mayza, respectively; their proximity to the top of their lineups provides enough volume to justify their spots. \n\nLooking at our bench, the absence of **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Andy Pages**, and **Jackson Merrill** leaves us without our primary defensive and speed-focused depth. We have carefully managed our game caps, ensuring that players like **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Lowe** remain fresh for high-leverage future matchups. We are monitoring weather closely, though no specific stadium warnings currently threaten our projected scoring. We will continue to track the late-season progress of **Nolan Schanuel**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Brady House**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Liam Hicks** to ensure our roster depth remains optimized for long-term category production.",
